        "content": "<p>I'm used to think of many elements of domain theory as a \"simplification\" of what happens in general CT where we only consider posets (so (0,1)-categories). For instance algebraic dcpos are the domain theoretic analog of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>ω</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(\\omega</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">ω</span></span></span></span>-)accessible categories. I realized recently that I didn't know any categorical analog to the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Domain_theory#Way-below_relation\">way-below</a> relation on elements of a dcpo.<br>\nHere is a tentative translation: let <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span></span></span></span> be a category with filtered colimits, a <em>way-below</em> structure on a morphism <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f \\in \\mathcal{C}(x,y)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> is the data for any filtered diagram <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">I</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{F} : \\mathcal{I} \\to \\mathcal{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07382em;\">I</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span></span></span></span> of a function <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi></msub><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mrow><mi>i</mi></msub><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mrow><mi>i</mi></msub><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">h_\\mathcal{F} : \\mathcal{C}(y, \\mathrm{colim}_i\\,\\mathcal{F}\\,i) \\to \\mathrm{colim}_i\\, \\mathcal{C}(x, \\mathcal{F}\\,i)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.84444em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">h</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5